  "body": {
    "givenName": "DRepOne",
    "image": {
      "@type": "ImageObject",
      "contentUrl": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/37078161",
      "sha256": "e1235556bc07344ba8d050bef21b6455553c91370eec7b572c5307c7b2cc8b93"
    },
    "motivations": "I have followed Cardano's development closely and care deeply about seeing its governance model succeed in practice, not just on paper. Working day to day in the blockchain space has shown me how important it is that voting power is exercised responsibly and with genuine engagement. I want to contribute my time and experience to the governance process, and to be a reliable, accountable voice for delegators who may not have the time to review every proposal themselves.",
    "objectives": "I believe Cardano's on-chain governance should be transparent, accessible, and driven by the long-term health of the ecosystem. As a DRep, my objective is to represent delegators thoughtfully by evaluating each governance action on its merits, considering both technical soundness and community impact. I aim to vote consistently, explain my reasoning openly, and help make participation in Cardano governance easier for everyone.",
    "paymentAddress": "addr1q9ur9smsmzzjgrnsulxx3naq9jgnh8eqnfp2f9eehm76c3z0v2famhkn7nv54fk35jd5wtssewzs7rpz6aazwkk5cmpsx6am26",
    "qualifications": "Several years of professional experience in the blockchain industry, with hands-on knowledge of the Cardano ecosystem, its tooling, and its governance framework under CIP-1694. Familiar with evaluating technical proposals, treasury withdrawals, and protocol parameter changes. Active participant in the Cardano community with a strong understanding of wallet and dApp user needs."
  }
}